Title: Excitations in Hot Non-Commutative Theories
Authors: Karl Landsteiner, Esperanza Lopez and Michel H.G. Tytgat
Comments: 16 pages, 4 figures, harvmac
Report-no: CERN-TH-2000-173
Journal-ref: JHEP 0009 (2000) 027
\\
  We study the dispersion relation for scalar excitations in supersymmetric,
non-commutative theories at finite temperature. In N=4 Yang-Mills the low
momenta modes have superluminous group velocity. In the massless Wess-Zumino
model the minimum of the dispersion relation is at non zero momentum for
temperatures above T_0 ~ (g \theta)^(-1\2). We briefly comment on N=2
Yang-Mills at finite density.
